git is version control system 

to link a repo with clone  ex. git clone https://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@github.com/sozoia/alx-pre_course.git
README.md is read me file 

Update your git identity : git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
                           git config --global user.name "Your Name"


git add .   to prepare any new file to be commited then pushed to server

git commit -m ""    this like a comment to till what the changes 

git push to upload in the server

branch is like an isoleted coby of your work    to add a branch --    git branch branchname
                                               to switch branch --   git checkout branch name 
                                           to see current branch --  git branch
                             

to push your work use git push 
if have upstream problem with push try this : git push --set-upstream origin new-branch

git pull is used when you want to make changes when there is another one making changes too (my understanding not sure)               
